PROBLEM: I got errors installing various packages (e.g. i2c-tools, aptitude) using sudo apt-get install. Some of the errors resulted in the following output:

Setting up dbus (1.6.18-0ubuntu4.3) ...
chown: invalid group: 'root:messagebus'
dpkg: error processing package dbus (--configure):

...

Package dbus is not configured yet.

SOLUTION: I added the line

messagebus:x:108:

to /etc/group (see http://ubuntu.5.x6.nabble.com/update-ubuntu-package-problem-10-04-2-LTS-td1254654.html). I then tried to install aptitude using apt-get install but got the errors

Setting up libpam-systemd:armhf (204-5ubuntu20.19) ...
start: Job failed to start
invoke-rc.d: initscript systemd-logind, action "start" failed.

...

Errors were encountered while processing:
 libpam-systemd:armhf

So I purged libpam-systemd using "apt-get purge libpam-systemd" (see https://plus.google.com/wm/1/103234494632951147878/posts/1UruGJiAeLz). I then executed apt-get autoremove, as suggested by the previous apt-get purge command.
